{
  "texts": [
    "The problems of education in war-conflict zone was studied by authors from different countries (Kester et al., 2022; Lavrysh et al., 2022; Cervantes-Duarte & Cano, 2016).",
    "Studying higher education in war-torn regions is vital for several reasons, encompassing both immediate implications and long-term societal impacts.In times of conflict, educational infrastructure becomes a prime target and collateral damage, resulting in profound disruptions that impede learning and access to knowledge.",
    "War disrupts the very infrastructure that upholds educational institutions.",
    "Schools and universities often face destruction or become militarized zones, rendering them unsafe for both students and educators.",
    "The devastation of physical infrastructure cripples the learning environment, restricting access to essential resources like libraries, laboratories, and even basic amenities."
  ]
}